HEADWORD: Enlight
<hw>En*light"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>en-</ets> + <ets>light</ets>. Cf. <er>Enlighten</er>.]</ety>
<def>To illumine; to enlighten.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which from the first has shone on ages past,⟦br⟧
<qex>Enlights</qex> the present, and shall warm the last.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enlighten</ent>⟦br⟧
